.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Alliance Poll</span><hr size=1> I think a smaller, more close knit alliance would suit our guild temperment better.<br>
<br>
Problems I have with the current alliance:<br>
<br>
1) &quot;500 Hibs at Excal!&quot; - Tons of misinformation on Achat. Almost no one bothers to verify anything firsthand and as a result we have the Albion equivalent of the Weekly World News. Almost anything I hear over Achat that ain't from one of us I disregard.<br>
<br>
2) &quot;Beavis has a PC?&quot; - If it's not horribly inaccurate information being broadcast over Achat, the usual broadcast falls into the following category:<br>
<br>
&quot;I like ....&quot; Fill it in as you see fit. Feel free to choose from the following nouns: strippers, boobs, Pam Anderson, fast food, liquor, whores, weed or any group that kinda sounds like Limp Bizkit. Followed by the inevitable argument over which brand is better, followed invariably by the people who actually want Achat material to be directly related to the game somehow, which in turn is followed by variations on STFU from both sides. I've noticed a trend here, it's usually one particular guild that starts this. Mind you, I'm not some prude. I group with Luna and Ranbas all the time and I enjoy the off color humor probably more than anyone. I just don't tolerate unjustified rudeness to strangers and that's what this boils down to. They wanna talk like this over /gu? Fine. But that's no reason for the rest of us to have to suffer though hours of drivel. I have Achat turned off for this reason specifically.<br>
<br>
3) &quot;The Forces of Midgard have just captured Castle X&quot; - This one I dunno, so I thought I'd ask: Is Achat actually that helpful in RvR? I see little coordination of attacks over it and other than using it as a LFG channel it doesn't seem like it has many advantages over the /y that usually gets people moving one direction or another in RvR.<br>
<br>
I KNOW we have good people in our alliance. When I used to have Achat on I'd hear 'em. Now it just sounds like a few little kids trying their best to piss everyone off simply because they can.<br>
<br>
I'd love to know what the other guild leaders think concerning this subject, as it'd be a shame to throw out the baby with the bathwater, but if as many people as I suspect are turning off Achat doe to these problems I'd say we're in need of a change.<br>
<br>
-Creepy <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6B8E23><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uaelis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aelis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(3/19/02 10:50:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=984.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Alliance Poll</span><hr size=1> While I don't really disagree with anything Creepy just said, I have had some good positive results from our alliance. I am constantly being asked to group by alliance members. Now that has nothing to do with AChat. AChat is an annoyance without question. I've sent 1 message myself because I was asked to inform our alliance of something by a friend. Other than that, I ignore it. <br>
<br>
I'd like to see AChat used only to relay reliable information or to organize raids. Up till now, I've not seen it used for any raids as all the raids I've seen are with members not in the alliance so a chat group is used.<br>
<br>
To sum it up, I don't think the alliance is a problem it's just the use of AChat. <p>Belenus <i>Paladin</i> Palomides<br>
